I have been using the pure body naturals shampoo for two days, I have shampooed three times and have to say I am in love with this product.

I probably wouldn't wear one out-and-about but I do use them for sectioning off my hair when I'm blow-drying, curling, or straightening it. I LOVE this kit. I try to make my morning routine as simple as possible, and usually go without most makeup. The only feature I'm not comfortable leaving natural are my eyebrows. They are blonde and almost invisible, contrasting unfortunately with my darker hair. And it is such a drag filling them in every day. With this kit I am able to wear my eyebrows by themselves if I please, or I can fill them in a little on the arch in much much less time that it would normally take to craft a perfect eyebrow from scratch.

The amount of color powder per capsule is way more than you need for one application. I only need a little "spoonful", grabbed with the edge of the included angled applicator brush, for 2 back-to-back applications to my eyebrows (I apply twice for a more intense result). What I do is I take a contact lens case, and break one capsule into one side of the case--then I transfer what I need into the other side, and mix a bit of developer. This way you can make your kit last much much longer! Remember, you can save the color powder but not once it's been mixed with the developer; close up the side of unused powder, and rinse out the other side once finished using the dye.

This product worked pretty well for me, but there was definitely a learning curve. The instructions said to leave the product on for 1-2 minutes, but it took 2-3 applications and leaving the product on for 10+ minutes for me to see any result. I am Bangladeshi and have darker skin, so that may be why. Also be cautious that this product contains p-phenylenediamine or PPD which is a common contact allergen that causes many people to have an allergic reaction. It‚Äôs not exactly safe to use on skin, and is typically used in hair dye. I was fine, but be sure to do a patch test beforehand. I also found it helpful to watch some YouTube videos of people applying the product with their tips and tricks before I applied it myself.

I love this eyebrow tint! First off, I want to say that I believe it's meant to tint the skin. Whether or not it is meant for that, it does that. I'm one that likes to fill in my eyebrows to some degree everyday even if I'm wearing no makeup. On lighter days, I'll just throw an eyebrow gel in there to add some darkness. Since I use this to tint the skin, after mixing equal parts powder and developer (may take a few times to know if you got it right or not),I use an angled eyebrow brush and fill them in as I would normally. This can be difficult if you're not used to doing this. It's important not to mess up since it will stain! I just keep a pointed q-tip on hand to clean away any mistakes and that works great for me. I fill out the ends first and work my way towards the center of the face. I only use what's leftover on the brush for the inside portion. I wait for 8-10 minutes and then wipe off with a makeup remover wipe. Most of the time, I do it twice (one time after the other) to get the color I want, since I don't want to overdo it. For reference, I am Asian with dark dark brown almost black hair. I'm sure if you have lighter hair, you'd do it for much shorter. I just experimented with it. I'll also note that it does nothing to actually tint my hairs, which is why I use it the way I do. I tried leaving it on for longer to achieve a darker color and that was a bad idea! I left it on for 20 minutes and it got all splotchy and patchy. I found that doing the two rounds of 10 minutes worked best for me. It also lasts only up to 5 days, which is disappointing, but still okay. That's why I rated this 4 stars - I wish it lasted longer. Overall, it looks great and is a very natural color while still making me look put together with nicely shaped brows. Love this!

Great product but just be very careful not to overdo it and don‚Äôt get it on the skin near your eyebrows!! Aim carefully at JUST your eyebrows!!

I have fine, curly hair, and use a Conair dryer with attached diffuser every day at home. I purchased this collapsible diffuser to use exclusively with my travel blow dryer (https://smile.amazon.com/dp/B00006IV22/ref=cm_cr_ryp_prd_ttl_sol_2?th=1) when traveling, and have used it a few times now. Overall, it works like it's supposed to and takes up a lot less space compared to my every-day diffuser. Some other reviewers commented about the tight fit when putting the diffuser on. I also had a hard time with this, but once it was on there wasn't a problem. Other commenters also mentioned the diffuser collapsing. I didn't have a problem with this, but I tend to hold the diffuser and not the dryer while I'm drying my hair. However, it isn't sturdy enough to lift my hair at the roots like my every-day, non-collapsible diffuser is. Pros: compact design (collapses to about an inch); light; easy to remove from dryer and collapse; diffuses the air like it's supposed to.

Cons: a little hard to fit over the dryer nozzle; not as sturdy compared to non-collapsible diffusers; not strong enough to lift the hair at the roots for drying.

This is exactly what I needed. I have a chameleon and I bought the push down from the top to pump type of continuous sprayer and it absolutely soaks everything down to a ridiculous degree. With this it's much finer mist, something my chameleon likes better. It doesn't freak him out like the other type and he quickly heads to his spot to get misted down.

One gripe I could have was I was wondering how this product works if you don't continually pump it. How could a non-powered sprayer continually spray off of one pump?.. Well you do still pump it.... It's less difficult than your typical pump sprayer absolutely, but you still pump each time to spray. Each pump though will spray for a short period of time before cutting off, maybe half a second to a second after fully depressing the handle if you pressed in one fluid motion.

I like it. I actually ordered this first and cancelled once I'd gone to the store and found the other sprayer I've mentioned. Now I wish I would've just stuck with this instead of wasting my money and having to order it again

Works well for sparse eyebrows and helps stain skin where there are no hairs ;) The longer you keep this on, the darker this gets (brown/black). If you have very sparse eyebrows though i.e. areas where there is really no hair, the dye will not last more than 3-4 days because it is on skin. The powder capsules can be opened and used in smaller amounts since you won't need a full capsule for each use, so this is a very economical buy. Carefully open the capsule, place the powder in the included grey cap, or on one end of a plastic soup spoon (easier to clean) and mix with the creme. That's how little you need.

My hair type: naturally curly. Medium thickness/density. Medium/long length. Very fluffy i use no hair products. I usually blow dry it straight after a wash and it lasts for several days before I need to wash it again.

PROS:
- Smells nice. Smells like the essential oils. It's very subtle, not perfumey at all, and really I can't even smell it after my hair is dry.
- Gentle. It does not irritate my scalp
- Cleared up my dandruff/scalp rash from my previous shampoo that irritated my scalp and I was always itchy.
- Cleans well. Some natural shampoos don't seem to remove all natural oils or hair products, but this one does.
- Even without conditioner, I can get a comb through my hair. Not something I can say about most shampoos.

CONS:
- Still need conditioner. I thought with all the oils are nourishing that I wouldn't need a conditioner, but I do.
- My hair gets oily faster. When using this, I need to wash my hair more often. I used to get 4 days out of wash and now I barely get two since switching to this.
- My hair is extremely static-y! It doesn't matter how much conditioner, leave-ins or serums I apply, I cannot get the static to go away. I didn't have this problem before this shampoo.
- Price. It doesn't do anything for me that I can't get from a cheaper shampoo.

OVERALL: The fact that may hair gets greasy fast and and that it's so static-y tells me my hair is too dry. I need a moisturizing shampoo. When my hair/scalp is properly moisturized, it doesn't get greasy and I don't get flyaways. I thought this was a moisturizing shampoo with all the oils in it, but I guess they all just get rinsed away, and then some. I will not buy this again because I cannot stand static-y hair.

I like the nice smell and size of this bottle. It has not made any large noticeable changes in my hair but that is a good thing because some shampoos don't pair well with me. I will say the push thing to get the shampoo did not work for a week or two then suddenly worked. Not sure why or what happened but during the time it didn't work it was very difficult to get the shampoo out due to the inflexible plastic of the container making it impossible to squeeze it out. But now it works and I'm good to go. I did receives discount for my opinion which was unfavorable when it was broken but not it is favorable.
